metadata.name: fxhash x thi.ng project template #866
metadata.description:
THIS IS NOT AN ARTWORK (at least not intentional)!

This NFT acts as a donation/funding mechanism for a new project template Git repo, providing a compact, ready-to-go scaffolding for generative art projects aimed at the fx(hash) platform/marketplace.

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

This template evolved over time and has served as basis for some of the author's own NFT projects (https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/toxi). The template is aimed at TypeScript (but can be easily adapted to plain JavaScript) and, at the time of writing, uses Vite as dev & build tool, ensuring an altogether great & speedy workflow with minimal fuzz.

(In the future, I'm aiming to provide an alternative version for more advanced hybrid projects using TypeScript, Zig (https://ziglang.org) and WebAssembly (https://webassembly.org/)...)

Framework agnostic

Even though several packages from the https://thi.ng/umbrella ecosystem are used to provide various essential overarching functionality, the template is organized in such a way that the main parts are completely framework-agnostic. You should be able to easily plug in your own toolkit of choice, however I cannot promise to provide support for this myself (though happy to accept PRs, also in terms of further docs, how-tos, guides etc.)

Example project

A tiny, fully documented throwaway example sketch is included, illustrating the following:

- Overall project structure & build commands
- FXhash related setup
- Static & dynamic configuration and state (re)initialization (via dependency graph)
- FXhash PRNG wrapper & utilities
- Canvas & SVG conversion/export/download
- 2D geometry creation, transformation & drawing
- Basic vector algebra example usage


Keyboard shortcuts

- space :  pause/play animation
- x : download canvas as PNG
- s : download SVG version

In case of doubt, it's this example project what is used here for minting. The funding, however, will be used for the further maintenance of both this project template and supporting my other open source work. 20% are also donated to the FXhash development team itself.

Thank you for your support! üôèüòç

metadata.name: Distant World #6
metadata.description:
A far away world lost in space where digital life is to be found either: gone, alive or desert. Variations include 5 palettes, disposition of buildings, sky and mountain backdrops and trees. 

Three modes with light, dark and the rare gold one.

- hit 's' for saving a 3072 x 3072 .png file for personal use

metadata.name: Connected City #51
metadata.description:
A cityscape in a far away world that is lost in space where digital life is to be found either: gone, alive or desert. 

Huge antennas capture space communications defining time and life habits of the population.

Variations include 5 palettes, disposition of buildings, sky and the city lights backdrop. 

Three modes with light, dark and the rare gold one.

- hit 's' for saving a 4096 x 2304 .png file for personal use

metadata.name: G. Masi #24
metadata.description:
45 years ago on May 12th, 1977 an 18 years old student was killed in Rome during a demonstration celebrating three years since the divorce referendum. As of today, no one has been found guilty for firing that bullet. Her name was Giorgiana Masi and her death shook the public opinion of the time.

45 years ago a close friend of my family, an artist that made a living with another job, created a painting that still hangs in my parent's living room and that has inspired me to seek art in all its forms. That painting represents an abstract human figure trapped in cage that takes a bullet while on the street.

This project is my digital reinterpretation of that painting and a thank you present to the first 45 among the holders of my other projects that will want to mint it.

- S key saves a PNG

metadata.name: Cradle #142
metadata.description:
Billions of years old, ancient remains decay across our Solar System. Mere transient visitors to our star, their ephemeral presence on our worlds is embodied in their creations. In the shadow of their megalithic constructions, we wonder what they might have brought to us.

They brought life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'f' - render at full speed
'space' - stop/continue rendering

The image quality gradually improves over time. The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.

metadata.name: Sunset in Paradise #209
metadata.description:
Hundreds of Walkers descend the screen drawing a sky, sea and the sun reflection; creating a twilight scene of a sunset or possibly a sunrise depending on which coast your paradise can be found. 
Features - 32 Palettes 
5 Possible background colors per palette
3 different complexities of sky:
	-Refined - 3 colors (25% chance)
	-Complex - 5 colors (25% chance)
	-Normal - 4 colors (50% chance)
2 possible border colors: 
	Matching the sun color (40% chance) 
	Matching the sea color (60% chance)
2 different stroke thickness: 
	Fine (25% chance) 
	Medium-point (75% chance) 
Different amounts of Walkers for Sky, Sea and reflection.

Made by @p1x3lboy in p5.js
June 2022

metadata.name: Organicon, variation I #23
metadata.description:
Generative art by Frederik Vanhoutte, @wblut
A unique generator creating an endless sequence of iterations with fixed features

Organicon, variation I is a slow piece, meant to build on the screen. Warning: the preview thumbnail is a pale shadow of live view.

Interface: a first mouse click clears the screen, creates an new iteration and enables active mode. In active mode each iteration remains on screen for a limited amount of time before being replaced by the next. A second mouse click disables active mode. In active mode a small dot is displayed in the lower right corner. '+' and '-' zoom in and out.

metadata.name: Teal Iron Elaphrosaurus #249
metadata.description:
"Teal Iron Elaphrosaurus" is part of an ongoing series of experiments combining hand-drawn "squiggles" and turning them into something unexpected.

Please be patient. It will take a couple of seconds for the image to render.

They are written by hand with Sharpies and p5.js.

metadata.name: Fleeting #71
metadata.description:
Fleeting, a generative abstract project that makes me think of missed windows of opportunities, the elusive perfect timing, and paths I never took. 

Press [s] to save a 4800 x 4800 px. PNG image. 
Made with p5js.


Collectors of any of my previous projects will receive one reserved slot per collection they hold. All unused reserves will be released on June 14.
